<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1909-07-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1909-07-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 16948/37.</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-07-14"><hi rend="italic">July 14,
                                        1909</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Mr. Thompson says that all legal process in the Juan de Dios
                                Rodriguez case having ended he has informed sheriff that the
                                prisoner can be had.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>